This article is a press gaggle by Press Secretary Robert Gibbs aboard Air Force One. The main topic discussed is General McChrystal's report on needing more troops in Afghanistan. Gibbs states that the President has seen the report and is in the process of evaluating the strategic assessments. He also mentions that a redacted version of a confidence report was given to the President several weeks ago. The President wants to conduct a strategic assessment before making any resource decisions. There is discussion about the possibility of a pullback in the mission in Afghanistan, but Gibbs does not provide any details on the options the President may consider. The press also asks about the President's involvement in local races and his upcoming appearance on David Letterman's show. Finally, the press asks about the three-way talks with Abbas and Netanyahu regarding Middle East peace, to which Gibbs responds that the goal is to continue building progress.